        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 11:50PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1149 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Canyon, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Tanglewood, Timbercreek Canyon, Palo Duro Canyon, Canyon, and
Mescalero Park.

This includes Interstate 27 between mile markers 96 and 112.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
